<div id="helpCenter" class="displays allResults">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
    <hr>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <h4 data-page="how_add_items" class="faqs">How do i add items to my store? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h4>
            <p id="how_add_items" class="faq_notes">Click on the <strong>Manage store</strong> menu, and click on <strong>add items</strong>. FIll in the item information and add an image , then click on add item button to upload that item.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4 data-page="how_change_price" class="faqs">How to change price of an item <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h4>
            <p id="how_change_price" class="faq_notes">Click <strong>Manage store</strong> menu, click on <strong>item prices</strong>. It display all your items with their prices. Click on the price of the item you want to modify and then enter the correct price on the pop-up box. Click on the check box or press enter key to compelete change</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4 data-page="how_deactivate" class="faqs">Deactivate an item <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h4>
            <p id="how_deactivate" class="faq_notes">If you do not want an item to be displayed for buyers to see, then you can go to your <strong>Manage store</strong> menu, click on <strong>item list, all items in your store will display with their availability status on the last column. Click on the disable icon to disable an item or click on the enable icon to activate the item again.</strong></p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4 data-page="how_incoming_orders" class="faqs">Manage incoming orders <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h4>
            <p id="how_incoming_orders" class="faq_notes">All orders made by your customers are sent to you via mail and on your clozeth dashboard too. To manage incoming orders, click on <strong>Manage orders</strong> menu, then click on <strong>pending orders, find the item you want to dispense for delivery after payment confirmatio from the customer. Now click on the delivery icon on the last column of the item to dispense the item for delivery.</strong></p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4 data-page="how_deliveries" class="faqs">Manage Deliveries <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h4>
            <p id="how_deliveries" class="faq_notes">After dispensing the ordered item for delivery to clients address, you should confirm if the order has arrived its destination. After confirming arrival at customers premise, its important you click <strong>Confirm delivery</strong> under the <strong>Manage orders</strong> menu, and then click on the check sign on the item to confirm delivery.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4 data-page="how_cancel_order" class="faqs">How to cancel an order <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h4>
            <p id="how_cancel_order" class="faq_notes">You can cancel an order that you do not have, not yet shipped or on trnsit. To do this, click on the <strong>Manage orders</strong> menu, click on the <strong>pending</strong> orders menu if the item has not been dispensed or click on <strong>confirm delivery</strong> if the item has been dispensed. Then click on the red plane icon to cancel the delivery to that customer. The customer will receive a notification of the order cancellation</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h4 data-page="how_contact" class="faqs">How to do i contact my customer <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></h4>
            <p id="how_contact" class="faq_notes">Your customer list displays the information of your customers, with their phone numbers and delivery address. You can call or chat on whatsapp if the number exist on whatsapp. <br>Click on <strong>Customer list</strong> menu to display the list of your customers. Click on their phone number to start chatting on whatsapp</p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</div>